@NODE Whatis "getsite - What is getsite"

@{b}                           What is getsite @{ub}

   @{i}getsite@{ui} is a short CLI-Command to Download URL's from the WorldWideWeb. 

   - You can use it in @{b}Scripts@{ub} to automate your Internet activities.
   - You can make a @{b}Workbench Icon@{ub} for the Scripts, so you will be able
     to access the Internet with a simple mouseclick. It will make no difference
     if the data is on your local system or on the other side of the world (except
     data-accessing speed of cause). Don't think ! Use your System intuitive !
   - Direct Access to Public Domain Software. Reading your favoured Computer-Magazin,
     finding a faszinating PD-Software with name and URL,simply go in a Shell,type 
     in getsite URL/NAME -d YOUR_PATH/YOURNAME and you will have the Software.
     I think it's faster and more comfortable than start a big browser at first.	

                @{b} The Internet will become a part of your system @{ub}






      @{i} Just take a look to the examples in the drawer "bookmarks" @{ui}



@ENDNODE

@NODE require "getsite - Requirements"

@{b}                      Requirements@{ub}

      Computer:   Any AMIGA
      Processor:  680x0
      Kickstart:  1.2+ for getsite Shell Command
                  3.0+ for standard viewer Multiview
      Special:    TCP/IP Stack (tested with MIAMI)


--------------------------------------------------------------

The Programm had been tested on: Amiga 500+/Viper520CD(68020/33)/8MB FastRam/IDE Harddisk/
                                 IDE CD-ROM/OS 3.0/MIAMI as TCP/IP Stack


Please @{"E-Mail" LINK mail} me if it runs or runs not on other TCP/IP stacks,if you have any
problems,for bugs report or just for fun.  

@ENDNODE

@NODE install "getsite - Installation"

@{b}                      Installation@{ub}

      Just copy the programm getsite to any directory with a path on it.

      for example :  copy getsite c:


@ENDNODE

@NODE usage "getsite - Usage"

@{b}                          Usage@{ub}

-Shell command

                  getsite [Domain] [Parameter]

                                    -Parameter: -d [Filename]     Download File as...
                                                -v [Command]      Select Viewer
                                                -r [Delay]        Auto Reload after
                                                                  [Delay] Seconds
                                                -l                Linklist 
                                                                  @{i}For Future Use
                                                                      Please Don't use @{ui}


          examples: getsite www.newsserver.de/news.txt   

                                                          loads the File "news.txt"
                                                          from the domain www.newserver.de
                                                          and shows it via Multiview


                    getsite www.raytracing.com/pictures/pic01.jpg -v vt

                                                           loads the File "pic01.jpg" in the
                                                           subdirectory "pictures" from
                                                           the domain www.raytracing.com and
                                                           shows it via ViewTek

                    getsite www.movies.com/mov01.mpg -v "mp -dither ham8"

                                                           loads the File "mov01.mpg" from the
                                                           domain www.movies.com and plays it
                                                           via mpeg_play in ham8

                    getsite www.pd_software/game.lha -d dh0:game.lha

                                                           downloading the File game.lha and
                                                           saves it as game.lha on drive dh0:              


@ENDNODE

@NODE icons "getsite - Workbench Usage"

@{b}                 Workbench Usage@{ub}


Just make a Script,draw a icon(IconTyp: Project) for it and sets the default programm to
IconX. Now you will be able to view a webpage just by doubleclick in the icon.

Hint: Take a look to the programm PICTICON by Chad Randall. It makes Icons out of Pictures. 

 
@ENDNODE

@NODE example "getsite - Some Examples"

@{b}                 Some Examples@{ub}

In the drawer "bookmarks" you can find some examples.Just Doubleclick them from the Workbench.
(NOTE: You must be online)

1. Money-Market Reports  :  
                            Here you can find Icon-links to www.stockmaster.com
                            Click on the Icon of the corporation and getsite will
                            download and view the topical chart of that corporation.
                            The chart will update every 20 minutes,so you can use the
                            -r Parameter to reload that chart every 20 minutes.So you
                            will be able to do other thinks on your computer and get the
                            topical data automatically.Another idea is to download the
                            HTML-Page from the stockmaster,extract the topical curse and
                            put it via ARexx into a turbocalc-sheet.     
                            


@ENDNODE

@NODE future "getsite - The Future"

@{b}              The Future@{ub}

     -   NOMORE BUGS 
     -   Maybe getsite will get a server/client suite.
         A host will run in background.Goes Online automatically.
         Counts the clients to see if no client needs Online-State
         anymore and then goes offline.
     -   will be able to goes offline if a client waits for reload.
         If the client sends the Reload it will goes online.
     -   Own Datatype viewer
         Reloaded data will be shown in the same window as the old one.
     -   will get links out of a HTML script.Shows that links in a list
         or create a temporary directory on your system.So you can access
         linklists like normal directories from the workbench.
     -   Cache Memory
     -   Only Downloads if the file is newer than the file on your Harddisk.
     -   A Tool that will creates Icons automatically.
       
     

